Coords_Features.title: Coordinates --> Features
Coords_Features.description:
Returns genome features contained within a specified coordinate range for the specified species.
(See also the Region Search tab.)
Coords_Features.constraintLogic: A and C and D and E
Coords_Features.name: Coords_Features

Domain_Proteins_Genes.title: Protein Domain --> Proteins and Genes
Domain_Proteins_Genes.description: For the specified InterPRO ID(s) or Protein Domain Name(s), returns the proteins and genes which have the specified domains or families. Results include both Swiss-Prot (reviewed entries known to have experimental evidence) and TrEMBL (additional submitted sequences some of which may be partial) sequences. Excludes proteins with no gene associations. (To see these, remove the gene symbol and id columns.)
Domain_Proteins_Genes.name: Domain_Proteins_Genes

EMAPAInteraction_Genes.title: Expression + Interacting Gene (protein-protein) --> Genes
EMAPAInteraction_Genes.description: List all genes that are expressed in a given structure/stage and have been shown to interact (protein-protein) with a specific gene.
EMAPAInteraction_Genes.constraintLogic: A and B and C and D and E
EMAPAInteraction_Genes.name: EMAPAInteraction_Genes

Feature_crossrefs.title: Features --> Cross References
Feature_crossrefs.description: Returns database xrefs/links for the specified genome features.
Feature_crossrefs.name: Feature_crossrefs

Feature_overlapping.title: Features --> Overlapping features
Feature_overlapping.description: Returns genome features that overlap the specified features.
Feature_overlapping.name: Feature_overlapping

GO_Interaction_Genes.title: GO term + Interacting gene (protein-protein) --> Genes.
GO_Interaction_Genes.description: List all genes that are annotated with a given GO term and that have been shown to interact (protein-protein) with a specific gene.
GO_Interaction_Genes.constraintLogic: A and B and C and D
GO_Interaction_Genes.name: GO_Interaction_Genes

GO_MFeatures.title: Functions (GO terms and children) --> Mouse features
GO_MFeatures.description: Returns mouse features associated with specified GO terms (and any children of this GO term).
GO_MFeatures.name: GO_MFeatures

where.value: GOTerm to Mouse Feature Annotations from MGI

GO_MFeatures_NoChildren.title: Functions (GO terms) --> Mouse features
GO_MFeatures_NoChildren.description: Returns mouse features associated with specified GO terms.
GO_MFeatures_NoChildren.name: GO_MFeatures_NoChildren

where.value: GOTerm to Mouse Feature Annotations from MGI

GO_Publications.title: Functions (GO terms and children) --> Publications
GO_Publications.description: Returns publications related to specified function (GO) terms, i.e., those cited by annotations involving those terms  (and any children of the GO terms).
GO_Publications.name: GO_Publications

GO_Publications_NoChildren.title: Functions (GO terms) --> Publications
GO_Publications_NoChildren.description: Returns publications related to specified function (GO) terms, i.e., those cited by annotations involving those terms.
GO_Publications_NoChildren.name: GO_Publications_NoChildren

Gene_Domains.title: Gene --> Domains
Gene_Domains.description: Show protein domains of a specified mouse gene or genes.
Gene_Domains.name: Gene_Domains

Gene_Expression.title: Gene --> Expression annotations
Gene_Expression.description: Returns expression annotations for the specified gene(s).
Gene_Expression.name: Gene_Expression

Gene_Interactions.title: Gene --> Protein-Protein Interactions
Gene_Interactions.description: Show protein-protein interaction data for specified gene(s).
Gene_Interactions.name: Gene_Interactions

Gene_Protein.title: Gene --> Proteins
Gene_Protein.description: For the specified mouse gene(s), returns the associated proteins. This includes both Swiss-Prot (reviewed entries known to have experimental evidence) and TrEMBL (additional submitted sequences some of which may be partial) sequences.
Gene_Protein.name: Gene_Protein

Gene_Proteins_Domains.title: Gene --> Protein + Domains
Gene_Proteins_Domains.description: Show protein domain information for the proteins of a specified mouse gene.
Gene_Proteins_Domains.name: Gene_Proteins_Domains

HDisease_HGene.title: Diseases --> Human genes
HDisease_HGene.description: Returns human genes associated with specified human diseases.
HDisease_HGene.name: HDisease_HGene

where.value: DiseaseTerm to Human Feature Annotations from MGI

HDisease_MGene.title: Diseases --> Mouse genes
HDisease_MGene.description: Returns mouse genes associated with (modeling) specified human diseases.
HDisease_MGene.name: HDisease_MGene

HDisease_MModel.title: Diseases --> Mouse models
HDisease_MModel.description: Returns mouse models (genotypes) associated with (modeling) specified human diseases.
HDisease_MModel.name: HDisease_MModel

HDisease_Publications.title: Diseases --> Publications
HDisease_Publications.description: Returns mouse model publications for the specified disease terms.
HDisease_Publications.constraintLogic: A and B and (D or E)
HDisease_Publications.name: HDisease_Publications

values: DiseaseTerm to Mouse Allele Annotations from MGI
DiseaseTerm to Mouse Genotype Annotations from MGI

HGene_HDisease.title: Human genes --> Diseases terms
HGene_HDisease.description: Returns human diseases  associated with specified human genes.
HGene_HDisease.name: HGene_HDisease

where.value: DiseaseTerm to Human Feature Annotations from MGI

HGene_MPhenotype.title: Human genes --> Phenotypes of mouse orthologs
HGene_MPhenotype.description: Returns the phenotypes of mice with mutations in the orthologs of the specified human genes.
HGene_MPhenotype.constraintLogic: A and D and J and B and C
HGene_MPhenotype.name: HGene_MPhenotype

Lookup_Features.title: Lookup --> Features
Lookup_Features.description: Returns genome features that match a specified string. (ID, symbol, name, synonym) for the specified species.
Lookup_Features.name: Lookup_Features

Lookup_GO.title: Lookup --> Functions (GO terms)
Lookup_GO.description: Returns GO terms that match specified search string.
Lookup_GO.name: Lookup_GO

Lookup_HDisease.title: Lookup --> Disease terms
Lookup_HDisease.description: Returns human disease terms that match the specified search string.
Lookup_HDisease.name: Lookup_HDisease

Lookup_MAlleles.title: Lookup --> Mouse Alleles
Lookup_MAlleles.description: Returns mouse alleles matching the given string.
Lookup_MAlleles.name: Lookup_MAlleles

Lookup_MPhenotype.title: Lookup --> Mammalian phenotypes (MP terms)
Lookup_MPhenotype.description: Returns MP terms whose names match the specified search terms.
Lookup_MPhenotype.name: Lookup_MPhenotype

MAllele_Genotype.title: Mouse alleles --> Genotypes/models
MAllele_Genotype.description: Returns genotypes (aka mouse models) carrying any of the specified alleles.
MAllele_Genotype.name: MAllele_Genotype

MAllele_HDisease.title: Mouse alleles --> Human diseases
MAllele_HDisease.description: Returns human diseases modeled by mice carrying specified alleles.
MAllele_HDisease.name: MAllele_HDisease

MAllele_MPhenotype.title: Mouse alleles --> Mammalian phenotypes (MP terms)
MAllele_MPhenotype.description: Returns phenotypes (MP terms) displayed by mice carrying specified alleles.
MAllele_MPhenotype.name: MAllele_MPhenotype

MFeature_GO.title: Mouse features --> Functions (GO terms)
MFeature_GO.description: Returns GO terms associated with specified mouse features.
MFeature_GO.name: MFeature_GO

where.value: GOTerm to Mouse Feature Annotations from MGI

MFeature_HDisease.title: Mouse features --> Human diseases
MFeature_HDisease.description: Returns human diseases modeled by mice with mutations in the specified genes.
MFeature_HDisease.name: MFeature_HDisease

MFeature_MAllele.title: Mouse features --> Alleles
MFeature_MAllele.description: Returns alleles of the specified features.
MFeature_MAllele.name: MFeature_MAllele

MFeature_Publication.title: Mouse features --> Publications
MFeature_Publication.description: Returns publications for the specified mouse features.
MFeature_Publication.name: MFeature_Publication

MPInteraction_Genes.title: MP term + Interacting gene (protein-protein) --> Genes.
MPInteraction_Genes.description: List all genes that are annotated with a given phenotype term and that have been shown to interact (protein-protein) with a specified gene(s).
MPInteraction_Genes.constraintLogic: A and B and C and D
MPInteraction_Genes.name: MPInteraction_Genes

MPhenotype_MGenotype.title: Mammalian phenotypes (MP terms) --> Mouse genes and models
MPhenotype_MGenotype.description: Returns mouse genes (or other sequence features) associated with the specified phenotypes (MP terms), along with the models (genotypes) in which the phenotypes were observed.
MPhenotype_MGenotype.name: MPhenotype_MGenotype

MPhenotype_Publications.title: Mammalian phenotypes (MP terms) --> Publications
MPhenotype_Publications.description: Returns publications associated with the specified MP term(s). These pubs were used in phenotype annotations.
MPhenotype_Publications.name: MPhenotype_Publications

where.value: MPTerm to Mouse Genotype Annotations from MGI

Organism_genes.title: Organism --> All genes
Organism_genes.description: Returns all genes for the specified organism.
Organism_genes.name: Organism_genes

Pathway_Proteins_Genes.title: Pathway --> Proteins and Genes
Pathway_Proteins_Genes.description: Returns the proteins and genes annotated to the specified pathway(s). Proteins include both Swiss-Prot (reviewed entries known to have experimental evidence) and TrEMBL (additional submitted sequences some of which may be partial) sequences.
Pathway_Proteins_Genes.name: Pathway_Proteins_Genes

Protein_Genes.title: Protein --> Genes
Protein_Genes.description: Returns the genes associated with the specified protein(s).
Protein_Genes.name: Protein_Genes

Publication_Expression.title: Publication --> Expression annotations
Publication_Expression.description: Returns expression annotations for the specified publication(s).
Publication_Expression.name: Publication_Expression

Publication_GO.title: Publication --> Functions (GO terms)
Publication_GO.description: Returns gene functions (GO terms) reported in specified publication(s).
Publication_GO.name: Publication_GO

Publication_MFeature.title: Publication --> Mouse features
Publication_MFeature.description: Returns mouse features associated with the specified publication(s).
Publication_MFeature.name: Publication_MFeature

Publication_MPhenotypes.title: Publication --> Mammalian phenotypes (MP terms)
Publication_MPhenotypes.description: Returns phenotypes (MP terms) annotated from specified publication(s).
Publication_MPhenotypes.name: Publication_MPhenotypes

Q_Allele_by_categories.title: Allele categories --> Alleles
Q_Allele_by_categories.description: Simple query form for finding alleles by "categories", i.e., by type, allele-attribute, and/or projectCollection.
Q_Allele_by_categories.constraintLogic: A and C and B and D and E
Q_Allele_by_categories.name: Q_Allele_by_categories

Structure_Expression.title: Anatomical structure --> Expression annotations
Structure_Expression.description: Returns expression annotations for the specified anatomical structure(s).
Structure_Expression.name: Structure_Expression

Term_Ancestors.title: Ontology Term --> All ancestors
Term_Ancestors.description: Returns the given term(s) and all their descendant terms.
Term_Ancestors.name: Term_Ancestors

Term_Descendants.title: Ontology Term --> All descendants
Term_Descendants.description: Returns the given term(s) and all their descendant terms.
Term_Descendants.name: Term_Descendants

_Feature_Phenotype.title: Genes/Features --> Phenotypes (MP terms)
_Feature_Phenotype.description: Returns the phenotypes (MP terms) associated with the specified  mouse genes or other features.
_Feature_Phenotype.name: _Feature_Phenotype

_Genotype_Disease.title: Genotypes --> Diseases
_Genotype_Disease.description: Returns the diseases associated with the specified mouse genotypes.
_Genotype_Disease.name: _Genotype_Disease

_Genotype_Phenotype.title: Genotypes --> Phenotypes (MP terms)
_Genotype_Phenotype.description: Returns the phenotypes (MP terms) associated with the specified mouse genotypes.
_Genotype_Phenotype.name: _Genotype_Phenotype
